<dec f='include/libavcodec/avcodec.h' l='4241' type='int avpicture_layout(const AVPicture * src, enum AVPixelFormat pix_fmt, int width, int height, unsigned char * dest, int dest_size)'/>
<doc f='include/libavcodec/avcodec.h' l='4226'>/**
 * Copy pixel data from an AVPicture into a buffer.
 * The data is stored compactly, without any gaps for alignment or padding
 * which may be applied by avpicture_fill().
 *
 * @see avpicture_get_size()
 *
 * @param[in] src AVPicture containing image data
 * @param[in] pix_fmt The format in which the picture data is stored.
 * @param[in] width the width of the image in pixels.
 * @param[in] height the height of the image in pixels.
 * @param[out] dest A buffer into which picture data will be copied.
 * @param[in] dest_size The size of &apos;dest&apos;.
 * @return The number of bytes written to dest, or a negative value (error code) on error.
 */</doc>
